Class ExecutionPlanCommand

  • java.lang.Object
    • dfischer.utils.ExecutionPlanInstruction
      • dfischer.utils.ExecutionPlanCommand

  • public class ExecutionPlanCommand
extends ExecutionPlanInstruction
    Data of a parsed command of the execution plan interpreter and the line number within the execution plan. Note: Commands can have 0..n arguments.
    Since:
    V5.5-D.
    See Also:
    ExecutionPlanInstruction, ExecutionPlanInterpreterInterface

        Create a new initialized instance.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the parsed command
        internal - mark if the command is internal processed (normally false)
        arguments - parsed list of command arguments. For commands with no arguments = empty list
        sourceLine - the source code of the execution plan line
        lineNumber - the original line number of the command within the execution plan file
